-- Citigroup CEO says sees no more management changes
-- 
-- Mon Dec 11, 2006 6:42pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/11/us-citigroup-prince-idUSN1125012320061211

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Citigroup's ( C.N ) chief executive said on Monday that the bank would not announce any further executive changes following its move to name investment banking head Robert Druskin as chief operating officer. 

 Speaking to reporters in a conference call, the bank's CEO Chuck Prince also denied speculation that Chief Financial Officer Sallie Krawcheck would leave the bank.